    public class CSVOptions

    CSVOptions is a concrete class for representing configuration options to import and export comma-separated values (CSV) data.

    • Field Detail

      • Default

        public static final CSVOptions Default
        Constant with the most common CSV import and export configuration options already set. The values for the various configuration options are defined as follows:
        • Row Labels: true
        • Column Labels: true
        • Ignore Empty Rows: false
        • Ignore Empty Columns: false
        • Delimiter Character: ','
        • Quote Character: '"'
        • Ignore Surrounding Spaces: true

        To include these default values when importing or exporting CSV data, simply include CSVOptions.Default in the import factory method or supporting TableElement export method.

        See Also:
        TableFactory#importFile(String, org.tms.api.TableContext, BaseIOOption), TableFactory#importCSV(String, CSVOptions), Table#export(String, BaseIOOptions), Table#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOption), Row#export(String, BaseIOOption), Row#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOption), Column#export(String, BaseIOOption), Column#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOption), Subset#export(String, BaseIOOption), Subset#export(java.io.OutputStream, BaseIOOption)
